items.title: Thirteen injured after demolition derby car hits crowd in Australia
items.description: The car was taking part in the race in New South Wales when it drove through a fence and hit the grandstand, police said.

items.title: Thousands protest against government in Mexico as clashes leave 120 injured
items.description: The protests came weeks after Carlos Manzo, mayor of Uruapan, was killed.

items.title: 'We're just going to go through this again': Americans fear second government shutdown
items.description: With the funding deal due to expire at the end of January, Americans are saving up to cope with no income again.

items.title: My mum was a 17-year-old free spirit - so she was locked up and put in a coma
items.description: Marina's mother was held against her will in a convent in 1960s Spain under Franco's regime.

items.title: Why India caps pollution reading at 500 when the air is far more toxic
items.description: India's air quality framework hasn't been comprehensively revised since 2009 and needs an update, say experts.
